<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="utf-8">
<title>{{ project.label }} — FactTrack</title>
<style>
  /* ─── Typography ─────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  @page { size: Letter; margin: 0.7in 0.7in 0.7in 0.7in; }
  body {
    font-family: 'Inter', -apple-system, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
    font-size: 9.5pt;
    color: #14161a;
    line-height: 1.55;
    font-feature-settings: "tnum" 1, "kern" 1;
    -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
  }
  .serif { font-family: 'Source Serif Pro', Charter, Georgia, 'Times New Roman', serif; }

  h1, h2, h3 {
    font-family: 'Source Serif Pro', Charter, Georgia, serif;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #0a2540;
    margin-top: 0;
  }
  h1 { font-size: 22pt; letter-spacing: -0.4pt; margin-bottom: 4pt; }
  h2 {
    font-size: 13pt;
    margin: 26pt 0 8pt 0;
    padding-bottom: 4pt;
    border-bottom: 0.5pt solid #c9ced6;
  }
  h3 { font-size: 10.5pt; margin: 14pt 0 4pt 0; }

  .eyebrow {
    font-size: 7.5pt;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 1.6pt;
    color: #6a7280;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: 0 0 4pt 0;
  }
  .subtitle { font-size: 9.5pt; color: #5b6573; margin: 0 0 16pt 0; }
  .small { font-size: 8pt; color: #6a7280; }
  .tnum { font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums; }

  /* ─── Cover ──────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .cover {
    height: 9.2in;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    justify-content: space-between;
  }
  .cover-top { padding-top: 0.4in; }
  .cover-wordmark {
    font-family: 'Source Serif Pro', Charter, Georgia, serif;
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 11pt;
    letter-spacing: 5pt;
    color: #0a2540;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }
  .cover-rule {
    height: 1pt;
    background: #0a2540;
    width: 1.1in;
    margin: 36pt 0 26pt 0;
  }
  .cover h1 {
    font-size: 32pt;
    line-height: 1.1;
    letter-spacing: -0.6pt;
    margin-bottom: 8pt;
  }
  .cover .subline {
    font-size: 11pt;
    color: #5b6573;
    font-style: italic;
    margin-bottom: 28pt;
  }
  .cover-meta {
    border-top: 0.5pt solid #c9ced6;
    border-bottom: 0.5pt solid #c9ced6;
    padding: 14pt 0;
    margin-top: 12pt;
  }
  .cover-meta dl {
    margin: 0;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1.4in 1fr;
    row-gap: 6pt;
    font-size: 9pt;
  }
  .cover-meta dt {
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 1.2pt;
    font-size: 7.5pt;
    color: #6a7280;
    font-weight: 600;
    align-self: center;
  }
  .cover-meta dd { margin: 0; color: #14161a; }

  .status-block {
    margin-top: 28pt;
    padding: 14pt 16pt;
    border: 0.5pt solid #c9ced6;
    border-left: 3pt solid;
  }
  .status-block.red { border-left-color: #b3261e; }
  .status-block.yellow { border-left-color: #b86e00; }
  .status-block.green { border-left-color: #2e7d32; }
  .status-block .status-label {
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 1.6pt;
    font-size: 7.5pt;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #6a7280;
  }
  .status-block .status-text {
    font-family: 'Source Serif Pro', Charter, Georgia, serif;
    font-size: 13pt;
    color: #0a2540;
    margin-top: 2pt;
  }

  .cover-bottom {
    padding-bottom: 0.2in;
    font-size: 7.5pt;
    color: #6a7280;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 1.2pt;
  }
  .cover-bottom .legal {
    max-width: 4.8in;
    margin-top: 8pt;
    color: #6a7280;
    font-size: 7.5pt;
    text-transform: none;
    letter-spacing: 0;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  .pagebreak { page-break-after: always; }

  /* ─── Section intro / pull ───────────────────────────────────── */
  .lead {
    font-family: 'Source Serif Pro', Charter, Georgia, serif;
    font-size: 11.5pt;
    line-height: 1.55;
    color: #1f2937;
    margin: 6pt 0 18pt 0;
    max-width: 6.4in;
  }
  .lead em { font-style: italic; color: #4b5563; }

  .callout {
    background: #f5f7fb;
    border-left: 2.5pt solid #0a2540;
    padding: 12pt 14pt;
    margin: 14pt 0;
    font-size: 9.5pt;
  }
  .callout strong { color: #0a2540; }

  /* ─── Tables ─────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; }
  table.findings, table.calendar, table.simple, table.tract-status {
    font-size: 8.5pt;
    margin: 8pt 0 14pt 0;
  }
  table.findings thead th,
  table.calendar thead th,
  table.simple thead th,
  table.tract-status thead th {
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 1.1pt;
    font-size: 7.5pt;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #6a7280;
    text-align: left;
    padding: 5pt 6pt 4pt 6pt;
    border-top: 0.75pt solid #0a2540;
    border-bottom: 0.5pt solid #c9ced6;
    background: #fafbfc;
  }
  table.findings td,
  table.calendar td,
  table.simple td,
  table.tract-status td {
    padding: 8pt 6pt;
    border-bottom: 0.4pt solid #e5e7eb;
    vertical-align: top;
  }
  table.findings tbody tr:last-child td,
  table.calendar tbody tr:last-child td,
  table.simple tbody tr:last-child td,
  table.tract-status tbody tr:last-child td {
    border-bottom: 0.75pt solid #0a2540;
  }

  /* ─── Severity / status pills (outlined, not filled) ─────────── */
  .pill {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 1.5pt 6pt;
    border-radius: 2pt;
    font-size: 7pt;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.8pt;
    line-height: 1.2;
    border: 0.75pt solid;
  }
  .pill.critical { color: #b3261e; border-color: #b3261e; background: #fff5f4; }
  .pill.high     { color: #b86e00; border-color: #b86e00; background: #fff8ec; }
  .pill.medium   { color: #8a6d00; border-color: #b9941b; background: #fffbe6; }
  .pill.low      { color: #2e7d32; border-color: #2e7d32; background: #f3f9f3; }
  .pill.solid-red    { color: white; background: #b3261e; border-color: #b3261e; }
  .pill.solid-amber  { color: white; background: #b86e00; border-color: #b86e00; }
  .pill.solid-green  { color: white; background: #2e7d32; border-color: #2e7d32; }
  .pill.outline-grey { color: #6a7280; border-color: #c9ced6; background: white; }

  .finding-title { font-weight: 600; color: #0a2540; }
  .finding-desc { color: #374151; margin-top: 4pt; }
  .finding-action { color: #4b5563; margin-top: 5pt; font-style: italic; }

  /* ─── Tract chain blocks ─────────────────────────────────────── */
  .tract-block {
    margin: 18pt 0 8pt 0;
    padding-top: 4pt;
    border-top: 0.4pt solid #c9ced6;
  }
  .tract-block .tract-label {
    font-family: 'Source Serif Pro', Charter, Georgia, serif;
    font-size: 11pt;
    color: #0a2540;
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  .tract-block .tract-meta {
    font-size: 8pt;
    color: #6a7280;
    margin: 1pt 0 8pt 0;
  }

  /* ─── Footer ─────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .footer {
    margin-top: 30pt;
    padding-top: 6pt;
    border-top: 0.5pt solid #c9ced6;
    text-align: center;
    font-size: 7pt;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 1.4pt;
    color: #9ca3af;
  }

  .scope-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1.5in 1fr;
    column-gap: 16pt;
    row-gap: 8pt;
    font-size: 8.5pt;
    margin: 8pt 0 16pt 0;
  }
  .scope-grid dt {
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 1.1pt;
    font-size: 7.5pt;
    color: #6a7280;
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  .scope-grid dd { margin: 0; color: #14161a; }

  ul.tight { margin: 4pt 0 14pt 0; padding-left: 16pt; }
  ul.tight li { margin-bottom: 4pt; font-size: 9pt; }
</style>
</head>
<body>

<!-- ═════════════ COVER ═════════════ -->
<section class="cover">
  <div class="cover-top">
    <div class="cover-wordmark">FactTrack</div>
    <div class="cover-rule"></div>
    <p class="eyebrow">East Texas Landwork Report</p>
    <h1>{{ project.label }}</h1>
    <p class="subline">Curative triage and chain-of-title examination · {{ generated_at }}</p>

    <div class="cover-meta">
      <dl>
        <dt>Project</dt>           <dd class="tnum">{{ project.project_id }}</dd>
        <dt>County</dt>            <dd>{{ county_name }}, Texas <span class="small tnum">(FIPS {{ county_fips }})</span></dd>
        <dt>Tracts in scope</dt>   <dd class="tnum">{{ project.tracts|length }}</dd>
        <dt>Leases examined</dt>
        <dd class="tnum">
          {{ project.leases|length + unattributed_leases|length }}
          {% if unattributed_leases|length > 0 %}
            <span class="small" style="color:#6a7280;">
              ({{ project.leases|length }} attributed to tracts,
              {{ unattributed_leases|length }} unattributed)
            </span>
          {% endif %}
        </dd>
        <dt>Wells indexed</dt>
        <dd class="tnum">
          {{ project.wells|length|format_thousands }}
          <span class="small" style="color:#6a7280;">(RRC EWA wellbore inventory only — no production data)</span>
        </dd>
        <dt>Examination period</dt><dd class="tnum">{{ examination_period }}</dd>
      </dl>
    </div>

    <div class="status-block {{ overall_badge_color }}">
      <div class="status-label">Project status</div>
      <div class="status-text">{{ overall_badge_text }}</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="cover-bottom">
    Prepared by FactTrack v{{ facttrack_version }}
    <p class="legal">
      All findings sourced from public records of {{ county_name }} County, Texas
      and the Railroad Commission of Texas. No proprietary or customer data is
      included. This examination is a curative-triage instrument intended for
      use by a licensed Texas landman or attorney; it is not a substitute for a
      title opinion.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>
<div class="pagebreak"></div>

<!-- ═════════════ FINDINGS ═════════════ -->
<section>
  <p class="eyebrow">Section I</p>
  <h1>Findings &amp; Curative Priority</h1>
  <p class="subtitle">Ranked by severity and confidence. Each finding cites the specific instrument and the chain-of-title rationale.</p>

  <p class="lead">{{ summary.body }}</p>

  {% if findings|length == 0 %}
    <div class="callout">
      <strong>No curative items detected.</strong> Public records reconcile cleanly against the registered rule set. A periodic re-scan is recommended; the rule registry continues to evolve.
    </div>
  {% else %}
  <div class="callout">
    <strong>Audit trail.</strong> Every finding below is supported by a search transcript filed under <code>docs/verification/</code> in this project's repository. Verification queries can be reproduced instrument-by-instrument against publicsearch.us.
  </div>
  {% endif %}
  {% if findings|length > 0 %}
  <table class="findings">
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th style="width: 18pt;">#</th>
        <th style="width: 58pt;">Severity</th>
        <th style="width: 120pt;">Rule</th>
        <th>Finding</th>
        <th style="width: 130pt;">Curative effort</th>
        <th style="width: 78pt;">Assignee</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
    {% for f in findings %}
      <tr>
        <td class="tnum" style="color:#9ca3af;">{{ "%02d"|format(loop.index) }}</td>
        <td><span class="pill {{ f.severity }}">{{ f.severity }}</span></td>
        <td><code style="font-size: 7.5pt; color: #374151;">{{ f.rule_id }}</code></td>
        <td>
          <div class="finding-title">{{ f.title }}</div>
          <div class="finding-desc">{{ f.description }}</div>
          <div class="finding-action">→ {{ f.suggested_action }}</div>
        </td>
        <td class="tnum">{{ f.effort_display }}</td>
        <td>{{ f.assignee_display }}</td>
      </tr>
    {% endfor %}
    </tbody>
  </table>
  {% endif %}
</section>
<div class="pagebreak"></div>

<!-- ═════════════ LEASE CALENDAR ═════════════ -->
<section>
  <p class="eyebrow">Section II</p>
  <h1>Lease Maintenance Calendar</h1>
  <p class="subtitle">Leases by primary-term horizon. Historical leases (term expired &gt; 5 years ago) shown for context; verify release on file before acting on them.</p>

  {% if lease_calendar|length == 0 %}
  <div class="callout">
    No leases in this project have a parsed primary-term end date. Clause-extraction coverage on this project: primary term {{ clause_coverage.primary_term }}%, royalty {{ clause_coverage.royalty }}%, Pugh {{ clause_coverage.pugh }}%, depth limit {{ clause_coverage.depth_limit }}%. Leases without an extracted term are omitted from this calendar rather than displayed as unknown.
  </div>
  {% else %}
  <table class="calendar">
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th style="width: 150pt;">Lease (lessor → lessee)</th>
        <th style="width: 75pt;">Recorded</th>
        <th style="width: 75pt;">Term ends</th>
        <th style="width: 78pt;">Royalty</th>
        <th style="width: 90pt;">Pugh / Retained</th>
        <th>Status</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      {% for row in lease_calendar %}
      <tr>
        <td>
          <div style="font-weight:600;color:#0a2540;">{{ row.instrument }}</div>
          <div class="small">{{ row.parties }}</div>
        </td>
        <td class="tnum">{{ row.recording_date }}</td>
        <td class="tnum">{{ row.term_end }}</td>
        <td class="tnum">{{ row.royalty_display }}</td>
        <td>{{ row.pugh_status }}</td>
        <td>
          <span class="pill {{ row.risk_pill }}">{{ row.risk_label }}</span>
          {% if row.risk_note %}<div class="small" style="margin-top:3pt;">{{ row.risk_note }}</div>{% endif %}
        </td>
      </tr>
      {% endfor %}
    </tbody>
  </table>
  {% endif %}
</section>
<div class="pagebreak"></div>

<!-- ═════════════ TITLE CHAIN ═════════════ -->
<section>
  <p class="eyebrow">Section III</p>
  <h1>Chain of Title</h1>
  <p class="subtitle">Chronological chain for each tract in scope. Only instruments directly linked to the tract's leases are shown; broader county-wide index entries are catalogued in Section V (Methodology).</p>

  {% if unattributed_leases|length > 0 %}
  <div class="tract-block">
    <div class="tract-label">Unattributed leases</div>
    <div class="tract-meta">
      {{ unattributed_leases|length }} lease{{ '' if unattributed_leases|length == 1 else 's' }}
      whose legal description could not be mapped to a survey/abstract in this
      run (back-references to prior recordings, non-standard format, or OCR-noisy
      text). Surfacing them here so they are not silently dropped from the
      examination.
    </div>
    <table class="simple">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th style="width: 70pt;">Recorded</th>
          <th style="width: 85pt;">Instrument</th>
          <th style="width: 170pt;">Lessor → lessee</th>
          <th>Legal description as recorded</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        {% for le in unattributed_leases %}
        <tr>
          <td class="tnum">{{ le.recording_date|default('—', true) }}</td>
          <td class="tnum">{{ le.opr_instrument_no|default('—', true) }}</td>
          <td>{{ le.lessor_text|default('—', true) }} → {{ le.lessee_text|default('—', true) }}</td>
          <td class="small"><code style="font-size:7.5pt;">{{ le.legal_raw|default('—', true) }}</code></td>
        </tr>
        {% endfor %}
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>
  {% endif %}

  {% for tract in project.tracts %}
  <div class="tract-block">
    <div class="tract-label">{{ tract.label }}</div>
    <div class="tract-meta">{{ tract.chain_entries|length }} linked instrument{{ '' if tract.chain_entries|length == 1 else 's' }} on file</div>

    {% if tract.chain_entries|length == 0 %}
    <div class="small" style="font-style:italic;color:#6a7280;">No chain instruments linked to this tract in the current scrape window.</div>
    {% else %}
    <table class="simple">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th style="width: 70pt;">Recorded</th>
          <th style="width: 85pt;">Instrument</th>
          <th style="width: 70pt;">Type</th>
          <th>Parties (grantor → grantee)</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        {% for entry in tract.chain_entries %}
        <tr>
          <td class="tnum">{{ entry.date }}</td>
          <td class="tnum">{{ entry.instrument }}</td>
          <td>{{ entry.kind }}</td>
          <td>{{ entry.parties }}</td>
        </tr>
        {% endfor %}
      </tbody>
    </table>
    {% endif %}
  </div>
  {% endfor %}
</section>
<div class="pagebreak"></div>

<!-- ═════════════ TRACT STATUS ═════════════ -->
<section>
  <p class="eyebrow">Section IV</p>
  <h1>Tract Acquisition Status</h1>
  <p class="subtitle">Per-tract readiness for acquisition or development commitment.</p>

  <table class="tract-status">
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Tract</th>
        <th style="width: 90pt;">Status</th>
        <th style="width: 60pt;">Open items</th>
        <th style="width: 60pt;">Critical</th>
        <th style="width: 130pt;">Royalty (extracted)</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      {% for row in acquisition_status %}
      <tr>
        <td>{{ row.label }}</td>
        <td><span class="pill {{ row.badge_color }}">{{ row.badge_text }}</span></td>
        <td class="tnum">{{ row.open_count }}</td>
        <td class="tnum">{{ row.critical_count }}</td>
        <td class="tnum">{{ row.nri_summary }}</td>
      </tr>
      {% endfor %}
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <div class="callout">
    <strong>Reading this table.</strong> "Insufficient data" is shown when no clause-level information has been extracted for any lease on the tract — the index scrape alone cannot conclude an acquisition is ready. "Critical" indicates one or more curative findings of severity = critical; "Blocked" indicates high-severity findings only.
  </div>
</section>
<div class="pagebreak"></div>

<!-- ═════════════ METHODOLOGY ═════════════ -->
<section>
  <p class="eyebrow">Section V</p>
  <h1>Methodology &amp; Scope of Examination</h1>
  <p class="subtitle">Per Texas land-services practice, scope and exceptions are stated here in lieu of a separate certification page.</p>

  <h3>Examination scope</h3>
  <dl class="scope-grid">
    <dt>Records examined</dt>
    <dd>
      Anderson County Official Public Records as indexed on publicsearch.us
      (lease, assignment, release, AOH, probate index entries);
      Texas Railroad Commission EWA wellbore inventory ({{ rrc_pulled_at }}).
      RRC monthly production (PR) and P-4 operator-history data are out of
      scope for this examination — see exclusions below.
    </dd>

    <dt>Period</dt>
    <dd class="tnum">{{ examination_period }}</dd>

    <dt>Examiner</dt>
    <dd>FactTrack rule engine, version {{ facttrack_version }} ({{ rules_total }} registered rules)</dd>

    <dt>Clause extraction</dt>
    <dd>
      Tesseract OCR (PSM 6) over signed publicsearch.us page images;
      regex extraction of primary term, royalty fraction, Pugh-clause language,
      depth limit, continuous-development language, and deceased-lessor markers.
      Per-field extraction on the {{ clause_coverage.total_leases }} examined leases:
      primary term {{ clause_coverage.primary_term }}%, royalty
      {{ clause_coverage.royalty }}%, Pugh clause {{ clause_coverage.pugh }}%,
      depth limit {{ clause_coverage.depth_limit }}%.
    </dd>
  </dl>

  <h3>Records expressly excluded from this examination</h3>
  <ul class="tight">
    <li><strong>County Clerk probate dockets.</strong> Probate cases in the seven East-Texas counties currently supported by FactTrack are filed in the constitutional County Court and held by the County Clerk (the same office that runs the deed records); only contested cases are transferred to the District Court under Texas Estates Code §32.003. The probate <em>case docket</em> — applications, wills offered for probate, letters testamentary, inventories — is not indexed on publicsearch.us. Documents that touch deed records (AOH, will-as-Muniment-of-Title, probate-deed-of-distribution) are indexed and are picked up by this examination.</li>
    <li><strong>County Appraisal District (CAD) records.</strong> Current mineral- and surface-owner identification has not been cross-referenced.</li>
    <li><strong>Texas RRC monthly production (PR) reports and W-2 completion records.</strong> Primary-term + continuous-production findings (rule r05) rely on absence of recorded release; an offsetting release elsewhere in the chain should be confirmed before treating the finding as actionable.</li>
    <li><strong>Texas General Land Office state-leased mineral records.</strong> Tracts with GLO interests are not currently surfaced.</li>
    <li><strong>Recorded division orders and JOAs.</strong> NRI reconciliation is presented as best-available; division-order accuracy is not represented.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Data sources actually populated in this run</h3>
  <ul class="tight">
    {% for source in data_sources %}
    <li><strong>{{ source.name }}</strong> — {{ source.description }} (last pulled {{ source.pulled_at }}).</li>
    {% endfor %}
  </ul>

  <h3>Statutory references applied</h3>
  <ul class="tight">
    <li><strong>Texas Estates Code §203.001.</strong> An Affidavit of Heirship on
        file in deed records for five or more years is prima facie evidence of
        heirship. <code>r02_probate_gap</code> downgrades to medium severity when
        an AOH is on file but younger than five years, and does not fire when
        an AOH ≥ five years old or any probate / RoP instrument names the same
        decedent.</li>
    <li><strong>Habendum-clause defeasance.</strong>
        <code>r05_primary_term_no_continuous_prod</code> does not fire when a
        grantor-side reverse-search has located a recorded release of the lease
        by the lessee; the lease died honestly and the chain is clean.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Standards &amp; limitations</h3>
  <p class="small" style="max-width:6.4in;line-height:1.6;">
    Findings are generated by a deterministic rule engine evaluating real
    public-record data. Each finding has a confidence score reflecting
    data-quality assumptions; values below 0.50 are flagged for manual review.
    Curative-effort estimates are based on East-Texas operator pricing as of
    {{ generated_at }} and are guidance only — actual cost depends on document
    discovery, recording fees, and any required attorney involvement. This
    report is a triage instrument and does not constitute a title opinion under
    the Texas State Bar's Title Examination Standards. A licensed Texas
    attorney should review any curative instrument prior to recording.
  </p>

  <div class="footer">
    FactTrack v{{ facttrack_version }} · {{ generated_at }} · {{ project.project_id }}
  </div>
</section>

</body>
</html>
